question.text: The F<sub>1</sub> and F<sub>0</sub> headpiece is a _______ and _______.

options.text: integral membrane steroidal complex and peripheral membrane steroidal complex.
integral membrane lipid complex and peripheral membrane lipid complex.
integral membrane protein complex and peripheral membrane protein complex.
peripheral membrane protein complex and integral membrane protein complex

solution.text: The F<sub>1</sub> headpiece is a peripheral membrane protein complex and contains the site for synthesis of ATP from ADP and inorganic phosphate. F<sub>0 </sub>is an integral membrane protein complex that forms the channel through which protons cross the inner membrane.
